- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper uses game theory to model the situation between the attacker and defender.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of compromising measurements on the electricity market and decision making in the smart grid.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of cyber technologies to improve monitoring and decision making in the smart grid.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss software engineering techniques for defending against bad data injection attacks.
